-- 
Zimbabwe to Get $600 Million From United Nations, ZBC Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-04-08T09:53:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/zimbabwe-to-get-600-million-from-united-nations-zbc-reports.html
Zimbabwe will received $600 million
from the  United Nations  to help boost economic growth and
improve social services, the state-owned  Zimbabwe Broadcasting
Corp.  said, citing UN Resident Coordinator Alain Noudehou and
Misheck Sibanda, chief secretary to Cabinet.  The $600 million will be disbursed from 2012 through 2015,
the Harare-based broadcaster said on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Durban at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 